The hard part about Gyromite was two-fold, the time it took ROB to grab the gyros from their holder, bring it to the spinner, then place the spinning gryo on the particular button lever without losing the gryo.  <br /><br />Stack-Up seems slightly easier, as ROB only has five colored cylindrical blocks, each of a unique color, to place on platforms.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=58">Great Hierophant</a> — Fri Nov 25, 2005 9:02 pm</p><hr />
