<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=786&amp;p=6969#p6969"><![CDATA[
Has anyone yet tackled the issue of ROB emulation? I've never seen the actual unit, nor was I able to find a clear description of how it works on the many NES nostalgia sites, but a previous post here says that it is not directly connected to a NES controller port - it works via reading flashes from the CRT. Have the flash patterns yet been reverse engineered? Also, how does the ROB communicate back with the NES? And what's with the weird plastic blocks that came with Stack-Up?<br /><br />Does anyone have a complete list of which NES/FC peripherals are currently not emulated? I can think of the following:<br /> * ROB<br /> * Miracle Piano<br /> * Power Glove (native mode; Super Glove Ball)<p>Statistics: Posted by Guest — Fri Nov 25, 2005 2:49 pm</p><hr />
